markdown: <::Cutting Longevity Test : chart : The chart displays a line graph titled "Cutting Longevity Test". : The x-axis is labeled "Number of cuts" and ranges from 0 to 70. : The y-axis is labeled "Depth (inches)" and ranges from 0.1 to 0.6. : There are two data series plotted: : 1. A dashed line with circular markers represents "Current DePuy Bridgeback 410". This line shows a general decreasing trend in depth as the number of cuts increases, starting around 0.45 inches and ending around 0.15 inches. : 2. A solid line represents "Current DePuy Bridgeback Modified to 420". This line also shows a general decreasing trend in depth, starting around 0.5 inches and ending around 0.43 inches. : A logo "SYMMETRY Medical. Othy" is present in the bottom left corner of the plot area. : The solid line (Modified to 420) consistently maintains a higher depth than the dashed line (410) across the range of cuts. : The legend is located at the bottom of the chart. : Current DePuy Bridgeback 410 : Current DePuy Bridgeback Modified to 420::> DM Source: https://www.industrydocuments.ucsf.edu/docs/rmwn0226 P-09686-00155 DEPUY023042075
